These questions are from:
Practical Tips for Software-Intensive Student Projects – HTML version available at http://StudentProjectGuide.info


We understand that duct taping a good camera to a cell phone is not a way to make a camera phone. 
Therefore, we want to prevent our project from being a combination of feature proposals.
What are some techniques we can use to help us realize what we want our project’s vision, scope, and target market to be?


Once we establish our project's vision, how can we make sure the vision and not a feature drives our project?


What is an example of a good reason why a vision will produce a successful product?


What is an example of a feature that does not match a project’s vision?
